title: Ó Cillín
text: Ó Cillín is the name of a family now rendered as <a href="Killeen%20%28surname%29">Killeen</a> (also <a href="Killian">Killian</a> and <a href="Killion">Killion</a>), found mainly in <a href="County%20Roscommon">County Roscommon</a>, <a href="County%20Mayo">County Mayo</a> and <a href="County%20Galway">County Galway</a>. It is derived from the saint's name <a href="Saint%20Kilian">Cillian</a>.
